Fix out-of-bounds access when `view->ndim == 2` (#249)

* Fix out-of-bounds access when `view->ndim == 2`.

The current code might assume that the dynamic allocation of
`view->strides` is followed by zero padding, but this is still an
erroneous access.

* Update workflows

commit.message:
REL: pass `python_requires` to `setuptools.setup` (#198)

* MNT: use underscore in `description_file`

because in the future `setuptools` will
require underscores.

* REL: pass parameter `python_requires` to `setuptools.setup`

in the script `setup.py`, to specify the Python versions
that `dd` requires.

The parameter `python_requires` defines the metadata field
`Requires-Python` that is specified in [PEP 345](
    https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0345/#requires-python).
[PEP 503](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0503/#specification)
specifies how installer tools behave when `Requires-Python` is
present and communicated by PyPI.

Users need to use [`pip >= 9.0.0`](
    https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/news/#v9-0-0)
and [`setuptools >= 24.3.0`](
    https://setuptools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/history.html#v24-3-0)
for the parameter `python_requires` to have the intended effect.

Relevant resources:
- https://packaging.python.org/guides/distributing-packages-using-setuptools/#python-requires
- https://packaging.python.org/guides/dropping-older-python-versions/
- https://packaging.python.org/guides/distributing-packages-using-setuptools/#classifiers
